From: Josef Bacik <josef@toxicpanda.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Feb 2022 10:03:29 -0500
Subject: btrfs: do not clean up repair bio if submit fails
Git-commit: 8cbc3001a3264d998d6b6db3e23f935c158abd4d
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
References: CVE-2022-49168 bsc#1238109

The submit helper will always run bio_endio() on the bio if it fails to
submit, so cleaning up the bio just leads to a variety of use-after-free
and NULL pointer dereference bugs because we race with the endio
function that is cleaning up the bio.  Instead just return BLK_STS_OK as
the repair function has to continue to process the rest of the pages,
and the endio for the repair bio will do the appropriate cleanup for the
page that it was given.

Reviewed-by: Boris Burkov <boris@bur.io>
Signed-off-by: Josef Bacik <josef@toxicpanda.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
Acked-by: Daniel Vacek <neelx@suse.com>
---
 fs/btrfs/extent_io.c | 15 +++++++--------
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fs/btrfs/extent_io.c b/fs/btrfs/extent_io.c
index 6a095e9962219..3f13ff0affdb3 100644
--- a/fs/btrfs/extent_io.c
+++ b/fs/btrfs/extent_io.c
@@ -2534,7 +2534,6 @@ static int bio_readpage_error(struct bio *failed_bio,
 	struct extent_io_tree *tree = &BTRFS_I(inode)->io_tree;
 	struct bio *bio;
 	int read_mode = 0;
-	blk_status_t status;
 	int ret;
 	unsigned failed_bio_pages = bio_pages_all(failed_bio);
 
@@ -2568,15 +2567,14 @@ static int bio_readpage_error(struct bio *failed_bio,
 		"Repair Read Error: submitting new read[%#x] to this_mirror=%d, in_validation=%d",
 		read_mode, failrec->this_mirror, failrec->in_validation);
 
-	status = tree->ops->submit_bio_hook(inode, bio, failrec->this_mirror,
-					 failrec->bio_flags, 0);
-	if (status) {
-		free_io_failure(BTRFS_I(inode), failrec);
-		bio_put(bio);
-		ret = blk_status_to_errno(status);
-	}
-
-	return ret;
+	/*
+	 * At this point we have a bio, so any errors from submit_bio_hook()
+	 * will be handled by the endio on the repair_bio, so we can't return an
+	 * error here.
+	 */
+	tree->ops->submit_bio_hook(inode, bio, failrec->this_mirror,
+				   failrec->bio_flags, 0);
+	return 0;
 }
 
 /* lots and lots of room for performance fixes in the end_bio funcs */
